	 <title>System.Replace</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para><symbol>Replace</symbol> replaces all occurrences of
		  <symbol>AOldString</symbol> with <symbol>ANewString</symbol> in
		  <symbol>AString</symbol>. <symbol>AOldString</symbol> and
		  <symbol>ANewString</symbol> are not required to be the same length. If
		  <symbol>AOldString</symbol> is an empty string, <symbol>Replace</symbol> always
		  returns <symbol>AString</symbol> (the empty string is not found in any
		  string).</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select "Let's play leap bunny.".Replace("bunny","frog");</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>Let's play leap frog.</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
